Want to achieve glowing skin? It starts with understanding your skin type! Here's a quick guide to help you determine your skin type and tips on how to care for it:

*Normal Skin*
Balanced skin tone, smooth texture, minimal pores
Tips: Use Gleem Beauty's gentle Nourishing Cleanser, with our Skincare Brushes to promote exfoliating before moisturizing 

*Dry Skin*
Tight, flaky, dull skin
Tips: Use Gleem Beauty's gentle Nourishing Cleanser, + Toner with our Skincare Brushes to promote exfoliating before moisturizing

*Oily Skin*
Shiny, greasy, enlarged pores
Tips: Use Gleem Beauty's gentle Nourishing Cleanser, + toner with our Skincare Brushes to promote exfoliating + One and done day moisturizer with our microbiome Nourishing Moisturizer

*Combination Skin*
Mix of oily and dry skin
Tips: Use Gleem Beauty's gentle Nourishing Cleanser, + toner with our Skincare Brushes to promote exfoliating + microbiome Nourishing Moisturizer

March is Self-Care Awareness Month, and we're excited to celebrate by sharing tips and tricks for prioritizing your physical, emotional, and mental wellbeing. At Gleem Beauty, we believe that self-care is essential for achieving radiant, healthy-looking skin - and it all starts with the gut-skin connection.

*The Gut-Skin Axis: What's the Connection?*

Your gut and skin are connected through the gut-skin axis, a bidirectional communication network that allows them to exchange information and influence each other's function. When your gut is healthy, your skin tends to be healthy too. But when your gut is out of balance, your skin can suffer.

An imbalance of gut bacteria, also known as dysbiosis, can lead to a range of skin concerns, including:

- Acne
- Dryness
- Sensitivity
- Inflammation
- Premature aging

Tips for Promoting Gut Health and Self-Care*

1. *Eat a Balanced Diet*: Focus on whole, unprocessed foods like fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats. These foods provide essential nutrients and fiber that support gut health.

2. *Stay Hydrated*: Adequate hydration helps prevent constipation and supports the growth of beneficial gut bacteria. Aim for at least eight glasses of water a day.

3. *Manage Stress*: Chronic stress can disrupt the balance of gut bacteria. Practice stress-reducing techniques like meditation, yoga, or deep breathing exercises.

4. *Get Enough Sleep*: Poor sleep can impair gut function and lead to inflammation. Aim for 7-8 hours of sleep per night.

5. *Use Skincare Products with biotics*: Prebiotics are non-digestible fibers that feed beneficial gut bacteria, supporting their growth and activity. Our *Gleem Beauty Microbiome Nourishing Moisturizer* is a great example of a product that combines prebiotics with postbiotics to support the skin's natural microbiome.

Synopsis ⬇️

It’s 2012, and post-revolution Egypt is sparking with political energy—but Hannah and Zain are numb.

The flight from New York to Cairo is long—longer still for two siblings on a journey to bury their mother. When they discover their father’s unforgivable betrayal, what’s left of their family crumbles.

Hannah gives up her spot at Columbia Law to remain in Egypt, where she navigates romantic entanglements and a new culture. Back in America, Zain’s self-destructive behavior begins to catch up with him, leaving him to wonder whether he’s any different from his father.

When the siblings reunite in Cairo months later, Zain is nearing rock bottom, and Hannah finds herself in the middle of the Arab Spring uprising. Together they confront shared secrets and reconcile their conservative upbringing with their new beliefs as adults. Will they heal together, or has the loss of their only bridge—their mother—set them permanently adrift?

A tender reflection on the effects of grief and loss, this deeply felt novel explores how siblings come together to mend a fractured family and, in the process, find themselves.

How it works and the recipe 

Ginger (Zingiber officinale) contains bioactive compounds like  gingerols , shogaols and  paradol , which are responsible for its medicinal properties. 

These compounds interact with the body in ways that can address pain and inflammation, common culprits behind headaches and general discomfort

Gingerols, particularly 6-gingerol, inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines (e.g., TNF-alpha) and enzymes like COX-2, which are involved in pain signaling. By reducing inflammation, ginger may alleviate tension headaches or migraines triggered by inflammatory responses.

Pain Modulation - Ginger affects pain pathways by blocking the formation of prostaglandins—lipid compounds that amplify pain signals. This is similar to how NSAIDs like ibuprofen work, though ginger’s effect is milder.

Improved Circulation - 
Ginger has vasodilatory properties, meaning it can widen blood vessels and enhance blood flow. Poor circulation or constricted vessels can contribute to tension headaches; ginger’s ability to relax these vessels might ease the pressure.

Nausea Reduction - Many headaches, especially migraines, come with nausea. Ginger’s well-documented antiemetic (anti-nausea) effects—linked to its action on serotonin receptors in ribbons gut—can indirectly reduce headache-related discomfort.

The Mindful Home 🏡✨

In the modern world, where stress levels are at an all-time high and sleep feels like a luxury, it’s crucial to create a sanctuary where relaxation is non-negotiable. At the heart of this is breath—the simplest, most effective tool for restoring balance in our bodies and minds.

Through our work with clients, we’ve seen firsthand the profound connection between breathing techniques and better sleep. Sleep is essential for overall health—it’s when our bodies repair, our minds reset, and we restore our energy. Yet, many of us struggle with falling and staying asleep. This is where breathing comes in—by simply focusing on the way we breathe, we can activate the body’s relaxation response (parasympthetic state) and prepare for a restful night.

Here are 3 powerful breathing techniques that have helped our clients unlock deeper, more restorative sleep:
1️⃣ 4-7-8 Breathing – Known as a natural sleep aid, this technique lengthens your exhale, calming your nervous system and helping you drift off effortlessly.
2️⃣ Box Breathing (4-4-4-4) – This simple yet powerful technique is like a switch to turn off stress and anxiety, promoting relaxation and allowing your body to settle into rest.
3️⃣ Left Nostril Breathing (Chandra Bhedana) – This ancient yogic practice activates your moon energy, cooling the body, and stimulating the parasympathetic nervous system, which is key to triggering deep, uninterrupted sleep.

But breathwork is just one part of the puzzle. As much as breathing can help you reset, other lifestyle factors—from the foods you eat to your activity levels, stress management, and even emotional well-being—are crucial to building a mindful home that truly supports your rest.

Your home should feel like a sanctuary for sleep, but this is only possible if you live mindfully. Listen to your body. 

At the end of the day, creating a mindful home goes beyond relaxation techniques—it’s about aligning your lifestyle with rest, nourishment, and balance.

This Father's Day, I have an amazing story to tell you about this^ amazing dad here.

But first, happy Father's Day to all the amazing dads out there from our GoodBrews family!

Founder Gabe here - GoodBrews wouldnt be possible without a very special team member: my dad!

The Story:
Back in 2023, when tech companies were having mass layoffs, I lost my job. That along with some family health issues made 2023 probably the most difficult year of my life to date.

When I told my dad about everything going on, his advice was to relax, take some time to think about what I should do, and reassured me that no matter what he'd be there to help.

When I told him about the idea of starting a coffee-for-good business where we use coffee to replant Brazilian rainforest, he surprised me.

He said, "I love it. How do I invest."

I said "well I need to do market research and find a supplier" and frankly a lot of other excuses that amounted to 'im not certain about this let's slow down' 

He said, and I remember it like it was yesterday, "The idea is great and I'm sure it'll work, but I want to invest in YOU." Safe to say I cried a bit 😅.

While hopefully it doesn't take a 2023s worth of tragedies to realize, I want to extend a huge thank you to all of the dads for the unconditional support and love. And to my dad, thank you for believing in me even when I didn't, I love you ❤️

In partnerships where one person leans more anxious and the other leans more avoidant in their attachment strategies, it can sometimes be challenging for anxious hearts (an endearing term I’m borrowing from my friend @anxiousheartsguide) to see their role in the dynamic. Their focus may be so caught up in what their partner is or isn’t doing, they can sometimes miss the work they have to do alongside their partner. 

The therapeutic work for anxious hearts often includes:

* Learning to express needs and feelings directly and without criticism or heat (e.g., yelling, pointing fingers, escalating gestures)
* Practicing taking time away from the relationship to foster their own interests and friendships
* Practicing self-regulating/self-soothing when upset
* Identifying and practicing healthy personal boundaries
* Developing a positive sense of self-worth
* …and sometimes, leaving relationships where a partner is truly unable to participate in a meaningful way

Do you lean more anxious in your attachment strategies? If so, what have you been working on to become more secure?

#Secure #Relationships

In our relationships, we have control over one thing: ourselves. We cannot control our partner(s), though changing our own behavior can sometimes have influence, potentially impacting the relational pattern or dynamic.

For example, if your partner tends to yell when they’re upset, you cannot make them stop yelling. You can, however, let them know that when they raise their voice, you feel anxious/flooded/scared. You can let them know that you need to take a break and leave the room. By doing this, it may influence the course of the interaction.

Regarding relationship issues, focusing on ourselves is often more empowering and therapeutic. Trying to change someone else can often feel defeating.

✨ What makes you energised?

you can’t have one without the other.

#intentional #ritual #dailyritual #rituals #intentionalliving #dailymotivation

I harp on about my morning ritual but this ritual, this ceremony, this practice - it is the most important daily devotion (habit, behaviour, routine etc…) I have cultivated for myself.

No matter what my day or life looks like, no matter what season of life I am in - I create some semblance of this ritual every morning.

Sometimes less intricate, sometimes more. Sometimes longer, sometimes shorter.
But there are some key ingredients that never change…

The key ingredients — silence, stillness, self-connection.

Silence - to hear, listen, get clear
Stillness - to feel, be, experience
Self-connection - to learn, understand, nourish

These are my non-negotiable’s.

I’m not sharing this in order to tell you how to curate a “perfect” morning routine for yourself.

I’m not sharing this to guilt or shame anyone who has spent years thinking they should be a morning person and then gave up thinking they’re just not disciplined enough to make it work.

I’m sharing this because - if there’s one thing I firmly believe in, it is that - starting our day with intention will change our lives (and therefor change our world).

But, it only becomes an all encompassing, life-changing practice when it is done ritually…

(aka, an act done regularly, with intention).

#intentionalliving #intention #selfcare #selfcareritual #rituals #selfconnection

We are all busy. 
We are all overwhelmed by our to do lists and schedules.
We all have other people to respond to and think about.
We are all paralysed by fear of what is happening in the world and exhausted by our unending responsibilities.

Because of that, it is easy to push intentionality into the back of our mind, promising ourselves we’ll book that yoga class later, open our journal tomorrow, turn off instagram in five more minutes.

But, these stereotypical examples of intentional acts are not the only times to be intentional.

Through (simple, personalised, actionable) rituals, everyone’s life can be one filled with intention.
It is not about the wellness podcast you listened to or the self-help practice you made time for (although it can be part of it, if you want it to be)

it is about showing up for your day to day life with intention.
It is about allowing intentionality to become a ritual - so that it is your default way to show up for your life.

I believe in ritualising intentional living because it allows us to embody intention in every and any moment.
It takes intention from a one time effort filled action, separate from our day to day life, — to an easeful joyful, every moment possibility.

Our whole life becomes infused with intentionality.

You are able to easily turn your two hour work meeting, your walk home from dinner, your phone call with your 90 year old grandma, into time infused with intention.

Because you have rituals that remind you, you have rituals to reconnect you, you have rituals to reawaken you.

When you ritualise intentional living, you are reclaiming your life.

But, for you, that moment could be any time. Find the time that can serve as that marker point for you - that moment that can lay the foundation for how you show up for the rest of your day (life).

My intention with writing this is a Call To Action - find a ritual (start with just one- it can be two minutes, it can be two hours) that you can seep into your daily life to support you living intentionally throughout the rest of your life.

What is that for you?

Rooted in utility, this season’s collection emphasizes performance and adaptability. A muted palette—drawn from the shifting tones of the Pacific Northwest—complements weather-resistant textiles and breathable natural fibers, with each piece designed to move seamlessly between environments and conditions.

The first delivery of our Spring 2025 Collection will be available Friday, March 14th at 9AM PST / 12 PM EST online, in-stores and on the HAVEN app.

HAVEN Spring 2025

As we continue to develop our design philosophy and expand our collections, the rhythm of nature and the dynamic environments that surround us remain a constant source of inspiration. As the seasons shift, so do we, exploring new ideas, shapes and iterations to guide you through the transitional season. 

The first delivery of our Spring 2025 Collection will be available Friday, March 14th at 9AM PST / 12 PM EST online, in-stores and on the HAVEN app.

This season, we refine utility with sophistication, creating garments that offer freedom in motion and stillness in nature. Built for function, and ease, each piece is crafted with technical precision—balancing protection and breathability, durability and comfort.

Whether navigating the urban landscape or embracing the outdoors, our latest collection continues to provide versatility without compromise, adapting to wherever the journey leads.

The first delivery of our HAVEN Spring 2025 collection will be available Friday, March 14th at 9AM PST / 12 PM EST.

A new version of a 2022 bill that recognises the legal rights of the largest freshwater ecosystem in the world has been introduced! The Great Lakes provide water for 40 million people in the USA and Canada but sadly, they’re plagued by sewage, industrial waste, plastic pollution and toxic algae blooms.

If made law, the Great Lakes and State Waters Bill of Rights will recognise the legal rights of these vital bodies of water to “exist, persist, flourish, naturally evolve, regenerate and be restored”.

The latest version takes on board feedback from local communities and expands protection to all NY State waters. It includes treaty rights protections for Indigenous Peoples and Tribal Nations and empowers counties and municipalities to enact Rights of Nature laws.

As the Rights of Nature movement grows, US communities continue to campaign to recognise Nature’s rights. The introduction of this bill at state level represents an important moment for this grassroots movement for change. 💦🍃🌍

Image Credit: Lake Erie | Shari Weinsheimer | CC0 1.0 Universal

It is overwhelming and aggressive and I cannot change it. (Also, with the sound off, this looks crazayyyy.)

To be fair, my oldest has expressed to me she prefers gentler love, so I respect her wishes. But it’s VERY hard for me. My middle and youngest love the wrestling and squeezing, so I let it all goooo. 

Where do you land with your love? Normal? Moderate? Aggressive? Do tell.

😴Also, SLEEP TIP: focused attention with your child where you slow down, put away your phone, make contact, and let them choose what you guys do can help lessen power struggles at bedtime. Give them even just 10-15 minutes a day of this individualized attention and say yes more than you say no during this window of time. Let go of the reins a little and give them the control and attention they so badly seek at bedtime.

I think this is my most unhinged recording yet. Enjoy. 

Sometimes things work until they don’t work anymore, and it’s OK to pivot and try something new. 

This was inspired by a phone call I had with a former client. Her child was clearly sending the message that she did not want to be bounced to sleep anymore, and when her mom gave her the space to fall asleep on her own, she did it without any crying whatsoever!

Maybe you have been adamantly against independent sleep, but your child is sending clear messages that they are ready for it. It’s OK to change direction.

To be fair, I have also seen children clearly sending the message that they are not ready for independent sleep, and that is OK too. 

There is no reason to struggle through something that is clearly causing more stress for your family than it is good.

If your child might be demonstrating signs that they are ready to sleep on their own, but you don’t even know how to begin doing that, send me a message or comment and we can discuss the ways we can work together!

Like Jim Carrey said: DO NOT GO IN THERE!

Change is hard and of course there are things you can do to get the water warm, but if you have been avoiding your child’s big feelings by taking over bedtime routine any time they show they’re upset with your partner, then you can definitely expect that those big feelings are going to come out once you eliminate yourself from the equation.

I am a very pull off the Band-Aid type person, but if you have an older infant or a toddler, it can always help to communicate in advance. I like to tell them, “I know you want mommy to do bedtime, but tonight, [your partner] is going to do it!”

As I mentioned in the video, you could also have your child choose specific days of the week where your partner is in charge of bedtime, and you could also have your partner gradually get themselves involved in the bedtime process by taking over one task at a time. However, even with that, it’s normal for there to be a period of adjustment once your partner takes over. 

Of course you guys should have a game plan in advance (any non negotiable like, if you have been making progress with not lying in bed with your child until they fall asleep, that should be the one boundary that your partner holds), but during the process, let your partner figure out ways to regulate your child on their own, without your involvement. And for those of you who are stressed out about the timing of bedtime and just want to rush things along, go into this expecting that it’s going to take longer than usual to begin with.

Consistency is key here, so know that it might be hard before it gets “normal” (I would say “easy,” let’s be real, you’re still putting a kid to bed at the end of a long day…nothing is easy anymore).

If you aren’t even in this realm and you are experiencing bigger issues like your child waking up constantly in the night, you being unable to leave their room, you wanting to transition them into their own sleep space, I have my Tackling Toddler Sleep Course at TacklingToddlerSleep.com!

The navel, often overlooked, is actually a fascinating part of human anatomy with profound significance. As our first point of connection to life during fetal development, it serves as a critical biological landmark that remains with us throughout our lifetime. Scientifically, the navel is more than just a scar from our umbilical cord it's a complex area with approximately 72,000 nerve endings that connect to various body systems.

In traditional healing practices, particularly Ayurveda, the navel is considered a powerful energy center. It plays a crucial role in our body's overall health, acting as a potential gateway for healing and energy distribution. The area around the navel contains important lymphatic and circulatory networks, making it a key point of interest for holistic health approaches.

Medically, the navel can be an indicator of underlying health conditions and is integral to abdominal wall structure. Its location corresponds with the body's center of gravity and is closely linked to core muscular systems. Some traditional healing practices suggest that applying oil to the navel can support various aspects of health, potentially improving hydration and stimulating internal healing mechanisms.

For those interested in exploring this aspect of health, navel oiling is recommended as a gentle, natural approach to supporting overall well-being.

Unstoppable. 🧿✨🙏❤️
.
In the early 2000s I auditioned as a model for Lakmē Fashion Week but was rejected. In 2015, I went back, except this time, I didn’t have to audition because I was on the jury of Lakmē Fashion Week. This past Sunday, the 30th of March 2025, I opened the Lakmē Fashion Week, 25yr Anniversary Grand Finale show, wearing none other than @taruntahiliani . 
.
To say I am humbled and grateful is no where close to saying enough. I am proud of me. I am thankful to God and the Universe for giving me the strength, endurance and patience to see my dreams come true. I am here to stay and I will never take the privilege of being in this industry for granted. 
.
There are so many thank yous to be said. Thank you to the backstage wizards @kamalmist @damandiaries @udit.jain102 @pemanervo @pujankapursharma @pooky24 @delnazd it wouldn’t be what it is without you. To @eltonjfernandez @eshwarlog and all the makeup artists I’ve ever worked with, thank you for making me feel even more beautiful and confident under your brush. To my dear friend @gautamkalraindia , my gosh love, how far we’ve come! To the legend that is @taruntahiliani , it was an honour to wear you. And to all the designers I’ve ever worn, thank you. To my team @aasawari_97 @dhruvipanchamia @hcmediamgmt @onlymuchlouder @takes_studio @dharm_maskai 
@ttejdatar thank you for ensuring that only the best comes to me. And of course, to my friends and family, without whom I would not be here today, thank you. And most of all, of course, thank you team @lakmeindia @fdciofficial @lakmefashionwk for believing in me and my talent and for giving me this honour. And for celebrating us is your Icons, I’m still pinching myself as I type this!
.
And @kripapateljoshi_official GIRL! You is the sweetest! This reel would not have been complete without that shot you took of me ❤️🙏 #girlssupportinggirls #womensupportingwomen

Test seats = empowerment, not shame. A lot of people think they’re embarrassing, but they’re actually one of the most helpful tools at any theme park—including Walt Disney World and Universal Studios. Test seats let you see what works for your body before you wait in line, helping you avoid stress, not cause it. No surprises. No awkward moments. Just peace of mind.

At Disney, the most used test seats are for Flight of Passage in Animal Kingdom and Tron Lightcycle Run in Magic Kingdom. Both rides have unique seating that can be tricky for some guests, so testing ahead of time can save you time and stress.

They’re made for you—use them. It’s not about judgment. It’s about feeling confident and comfortable so you can enjoy your day without worry. Your experience matters, and you deserve to ride with confidence—whether you're visiting Disney or Universal.

Want more tips to help you feel empowered at theme parks? Follow for plus-size friendly ride checks, honest advice, and real talk that puts your comfort first.

So this is where we are: A viral “challenge” to ask AI to create a representation of yourself. 

The result? 

Riddled with inaccuracies. Strangely idealized. Curiously captivating.

It stops you in your tracks—to see yourself through the lens of the machine. 

Flattened into a fantasy. A bizarre version of you, pretending to be you, rendered with the snap of a finger.

This is artificial intimacy. And this moment—this image—is a mirror of the MetaCrisis.

When our identities are constructed through algorithms, and our relationships increasingly mediated by screens, we must ask:
🔹 What does it mean to relate in a world of digital projection?
🔹 Where do we locate the real, the vulnerable, the human?

These aren’t just musings. They’re the urgent questions of our time.

And they’re exactly what we’ll be unpacking at Sessions Live 2025: Mating in the Metacrisis.

“In the summer of 1998, while directing a celebrity photoshoot in New York City for a magazine I was editor of, I remember glancing at the small television in the corner of the room while we were waiting for our star to change looks when a stunning young woman appeared on the screen holding a gaudy MTV microphone. Though the set’s sound was muted, the engaging House Of Style co-host (alongside fellow model/thespian Rebecca Romijn) captured my attention instantly without hearing her utter a sound. Then her name appeared in the chyron at the bottom of the screen: James King. What?! Could this really be her name? Oh, I do like me some rule breakers. I fell instantly in love with this James King, burgeoning pop culture icon.”
Richard Perez Féria

Shawn Marshall "altar" 12 x 12" collage on panel up now as part of "Stills."

Marshall writes "I'm both a preacher's daughter and a missionary kid. My parents moved our family overseas when I was 9 months old. We lived in Cyprus until the Turkish bombed it. We lost most of our things. When we moved to Beirut, Lebanon, the civil war started not long after. We endured bombs and rocket launches until we evacuated in 1975. We moved back to the US when I was almost 8, and my dad later became the head of the Kentucky Baptist Convention. Religion has played a big role in my life but often not in good ways.

I don't practice any religion but do consider myself deeply spiritual - continually searching for meaning and resolve. Many of these pieces reflect of my feelings about the confines of the Christian religion and meanings placed on religious iconography.

The pieces with women in those spaces are a reaction against the role women are expected to have in the church."

Friendships fade. And that’s okay.

Not every bond is meant to last forever. Friendships can shift as we evolve, making space for who we are becoming. The reasons are endless:

- Life commitments pull us in different directions.
- Shared interests fade as we grow.
- Sometimes, the connection just doesn’t feel the same anymore.

The important thing is to recognise when it’s time to let go with grace. Clinging to what no longer serves us can stop us from moving forward. Not everyone is meant to stay, and that’s part of life’s flow 🌻

‘How to Stop Breaking Your Own Heart’ explores the beauty of acceptance, the art of letting go, and how to honour connections without holding onto them past their season.

This one is worth the read 📖

The situation : this client came with complaints that her lashes were sore, and she had poor retention. 

The truth : her lashes were glued together, she was not educated on natural lash health and the maintenance or cleansing routine required of extensions. 

The goal : healthy full lashes, 4 week retention, and education on proper home maintenance. 

• first • I deep cleansed with occusoft platnium to exfoliate the presumed ‘years’ of dirt oil makeup etc. then set to removing any poorly placed extensions. 

• second • we did a full set of wispy light extensions for fullness while keeping her natural lash health a top priority. We lashed EVERY SINGLE LASH. Giving her a nice full and guaranteed long lasting retention. 

• third • we sent this client home with a complimentary bottle of lash cleanser, a cleansing brush, a detailed maintenance plan, and access to our 24/7 customer service line for any issues or questions. 

💠 In 9 years I’ve always believed I could lash over anything, in walks this client. I believe clients like this continue to teach •ME• how to do better. How to educate more, and how to reverse damage that was done previously. 

💠 I used to not work over another artists work, but what did that do? Impede me from gaining more confidence in my craft, decrease my knowledge for troubleshooting, and hinder me from fostering new friendships. 

The Moral : if you’re unhappy with your lash retention, I’d love to help troubleshoot and get your lashes perfect for you! Most clients go 3-5 weeks between maintenance appointments 🫶🏻

SEVEN WAYS TO USE HAIR GEL ON TEXTURED HAIR.

1. SLICK BACK STYLES | We know you see all those cute slick back #ponytails styles populating on TikTok! Having a good gel to mold your hair is major 🔑.

2. EDGES & BABY HAIR | Swoops and woops around your hair line will add some sass to just about any hairstyle- whether it's a #puff, #washngo, or slick back ponytail. We have our #lemongrassslayandlayedgegel but a good gel like our #lemongrassholditstylinggel is a great option too!

3. PROTECTIVE STYLES & LOC RETWISTS | If you notice the foundation to a good protective style is how you prep and lay the hair closest to your scalp. Using a thicker product like gel, edge control, or pomade is so helpful and ensures your style lasts longer! It's great for your flyaways too!

4. WASH N' GO | Using a hair gel for wash n' gos almost makes the style live up to it's name- literally wash and go! It will make your curls pop and last longer!

5. ROD SETS | Using a mousse is more ideal however add a bit of gel to the ends to make sure the curls that shape your #afro are a bit MORE defined and crisp!

6. FINGERWAVES | Where are our #TWA girls at? You have to try #fingerwaves at least a few times before your hair grows out! If you can't achieve this style with mousse GEL is your friend!

7. WIG INSTALL | If you're not a fan of glue and sprays our Hold It Styling Gel is a great option to melt down your lace with lasting hold! Try it and share your experience with us!

Four simple high quality ingredients are used in this beautifully light yet flavoursome dish. Frying the culatello ham (you could substitute Parma Ham if needs be) brings an intense flavour and wonderful crispiness to it, complimenting the creamy burrata and Pesto Barilla alla Genovese, which combined with the Barilla Spaghetti, makes for a perfect light dish.
 
Ingredients:
160 g Barilla Spaghetti
50g Culatello raw ham, thinly sliced into 3mm ribbons
100g Pesto Barilla alla Genovese 
100 g burrata
 
Method:
1. Bring a pot of salted water to a boil and cook the Barilla Rigatoni according to packet instructions, until al dente.
2. Drain and remove from the heat.
3. Meanwhile, heat a skillet until medium hot. Add the Culatello ham and fry until crispy and golden. Remove from the pan, discarding any fat.
4. Toss the pasta with the Barilla Basilico Genovese 
5. Divide between serving plates and top with the crispy Culatello and torn pieces and burrata.
6. Serve hot.

#SoCreamyYouCantResist #Barilla

Imagine the surprise when you realise you can use Barilla Al Bronzo pasta to wipe your plate…​

#BarillaAlBronzo the pasta that does #Scarpetta

Roman pinsa are perfect as a light lunch or supper. Here they’re topped with brie and toasted in the oven, before being drizzled with Pesto Barilla alla Genovese. Lightly marinated paper-thin asparagus strips and Parma ham are then piled on top giving a classic delicious flavour combination.
 
Ingredients:
2 Roman pinsa, or demi baguettes, split in half
80g brie, sliced
1 lime, zested and juiced
2 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
pink peppercorns, lightly crushed
sea salt 
8 green asparagus, trimmed and peeled lengthwise into strips
1 jar (190g) Pesto Barilla alla Genovese 
200g Parma ham, cut into strips
 
Method: 
1. Preheat the oven to 200°C, fan 180°C, gas mark 4.
2. Lay the pinsa onto a baking sheet and top with the brie.
3. Place in the oven for 7 minutes until hot through.
4. Meanwhile, tip the lime zest and juice and olive oil into a bowl and whisk to combine.
5. Season with pink peppercorns and salt then add the asparagus strips and toss to coat. Set aside to marinate for a few minutes until the pinch is hot.
6. Spoon the Pesto Barilla alla Genovese over the toasted pinsa then top with the marinated asparagus and Parma ham.
7. Serve straight away whilst hot.

Crispy artichoke leaves compliment the Pesto Barilla alla Genovese tossed fusilli, giving a wonderfully crispy element to it. Finished with plenty of grated smoked ricotta, the whole dish has a great complexity and earthiness to it.

Ingredients:
160g Fusilli Barilla
Vegetable oil
2 globe artichokes, cleaned and leaves separated, discarding outer tough leaves
1 lemon, juice
Sea salt
100g Pesto Barilla alla Genovese
40g smoked ricotta, finely grated
 
Method:
1. Bring a pot of salted water to a boil and cook the Barilla Fusilli according to packet instructions, until al dente.
2. Drain and remove from the heat.
3. Meanwhile, as you prepare the artichoke, drop the tender leaves into a bowl of water with the lemon juice, to prevent discolouration whilst you prepare the rest of them.
4. Add enough oil to a deep sided pan to fill 3cm deep. Heat to about medium hot (180°C) and fry the leaves in batches, for 2-3 minutes, until golden brown and crispy.
5. Drain onto a kitchen paper lined plate then season with salt.
6. Tip the cooked pasta into a large bowl and toss with the Pesto Barilla alla Genovese until coated.
7. Divide between serving dishes and top with the crispy artichoke leaves followed by the smoked ricotta.

✨ Montenegro Travel Tips:

🏰 Base yourself in Kotor to wander medieval alleys, hike to the fortress, and wake up to dreamy bay views
🛣️ Take the Serpentine Road for a scenic drive full of switchbacks and jaw-dropping panoramas
🥾 Lace up your boots for Durmitor National Park, where glacial lakes and alpine peaks steal the show
🌊 Swim in the turquoise waters near Sveti Stefan, or catch the perfect photo from a cliffside viewpoint
🚤 Hop on a boat to Our Lady of the Rocks, a tiny island church built on legend and limestone
🍯 Try local favorites like octopus salad and priganice (fried dough) drizzled with honey at Konoba Catovica Mlini
☀️ Plan your visit for late May or early October for fewer tourists, perfect temps, and golden light

🐫 Stand in awe of the Pyramids of Giza & Sphinx 
 🏨 Wake up to views of the pyramids at Marriott Mena House 
🛍️ Wander the buzzing alleys of Khan el-Khalili market 
🏺 See ancient royalty up close at the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization 
⛪ Experience the powerful contrast of the Cave Church, tucked behind “Garbage City” 

✨ Sharm el-Sheikh (three days):
🌊 Unwind at a beachside resort on the Red Sea 
🏮 Get to Farsha Café early for front-row sunset views & an epic light show 
🏙️ Shop and stroll along lively Naama Bay 
🕌 Admire the intricate architecture of Al-Sahaba Mosque 

✨ Aswan (four days):
🌅 Take a sunrise trip to the awe-inspiring Abu Simbel 
🌴 Check into the historic Sofitel Old Cataract Hotel for Nile views 
⛵ Sail past Elephantine Island on a river cruise 
⛴️ Catch golden hour on a peaceful felucca ride 
🧡 Get a taste of local life at the colorful Nubian Village

✨ Luxor (one day):
👑 Enter the tombs at the Valley of the Kings, including King Tut's 
🏛️ Marvel at the scale of Karnak, Luxor, and Hatshepsut Temples 

Which stop are you most excited to experience? 🤩

If you're going to add one destination to your African bucket list, let it be Zanzibar, Tanzania! 🇹🇿 🏝️. This dreamy island, just off the coast of Tanzania in East Africa, offers a little bit of everything. Here's what you can't miss:

🏝 Relax on Nungwi & Kendwa’s turquoise beaches, perfect for lazy days and dreamy sunsets
🕌 Explore Stone Town, a UNESCO World Heritage site packed with history, culture, and spice-filled alleyways
🌶️ Join a spice farm tour and learn why Zanzibar is nicknamed the “Spice Island”
🐢 Hop over to Prison Island and meet giant tortoises and snorkel clear waters
🐬 Enjoy dolphin spotting in Kizimkazi or snorkel the vibrant Mnemba Atoll
🧘‍♀️ Stay beachside in boho bungalows or barefoot luxury resorts

Zanzibar blends Swahili culture, Indian Ocean beauty, and a laid-back vibe that’s hard to beat! Who's catching the next flight over? ✈️ 🇹🇿 🏝️

When wildfires swept through Los Angeles, thousands were forced to evacuate — including older adults in long-term care who rely on daily medication.

🤝 That’s when #TeamCVS jumped into action.

They rerouted deliveries in real time, navigated road closures and worked around the clock to help ensure every prescription got to the right place. Because missing even one dose could be life-threatening.

🙌 We’re grateful for the teammates who go the extra mile, even in moments of crisis. Read the full story at the #LinkInBio.

For 29 years, Denise Zachmann has shown what it means to lead with heart. This #NationalVolunteerWeek, we’re celebrating how she brings that care and compassion to everything she does, including:

🧵 Leading a sewing team with 40+ volunteers crafting mastectomy pillows and head scarves for cancer patients.

📦 Organizing household essentials donations for families in Hartford, CT.

🤝 Creating space for colleagues to give back in ways that work for them.

Thanks for reminding us that community starts with each of us, Denise.

Queerie With…Zolita! 💕

Tune into “Queerie With...” TONIGHT at 3PM PST/6:00 PM EST where we will be chatting with pop sensation @zolita! 💜✨⁠
⁠
For emerging alt-pop icon Zolita, every song begins as an elaborate movie in her mind, irresistibly rooted in both riveting drama and viscerally real feeling. A truly multidimensional artist, the L.A.-based singer/songwriter/filmmaker matches her fiercely honest musical output with self-directed videos, each revealing her singular aesthetic. Zolita now shares "Ashley,” the second single off of her upcoming EP, Falling Out / Falling In, set to release in February 2023. ⁠
⁠
Continuing with her massively successful and totally self-made approach, "Ashley" will be accompanied by a cinematic, self-directed and self-edited music video centering the queer love storyline that is ever present throughout the entirety of the EP. Most famously known for the viral trilogy that she previously released which included "I F*cking Love you", "Somebody I F*cked Once" & "Single In September," the multi-hyphenate has amassed over 50 million streams, 140 million video views, and 1 million in social audience to date. Today in History: The Selma to Montgomery March Begins ✊🏾⁠
⁠
On March 21, 1965, thousands of brave souls set out on a 54-mile journey from Selma to Montgomery, demanding the right to vote. Led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., this march was a defining moment in the Civil Rights Movement, one that helped pave the way for the Voting Rights Act of 1965.⁠
⁠
The road wasn’t easy, but they marched anyway. They marched for justice, for equality, and for the generations that would come after them.⁠
⁠
Today, we honor their courage and their sacrifice. The fight for our rights didn’t end in 1965, and it’s on us to keep pushing forward. 💪🏾 #BlackHistory⁠

This weekend, Alexis Magner took on one of cycling’s most iconic races, the Tour of Flanders, and came out swinging💥

Flanders is no easy feat. It’s a battle of positioning, patience, and power, and Alexis showed up with all three, finishing as the 2nd highest-placing American🇺🇲🔥 

Here’s what Alexis had to say👇: 
“I had race nerves, but they were more out of excitement than pressure to get a result. My training has been going really well and being able to race Flanders and get that big load is an important building block for my fitness. I broke the race up into pieces—focusing on positioning for each section and making the front group. I knew that if I kept ticking off those milestones, then I had a chance of making it pretty far into the race. I finally blew on the Taaienberg. I did come back to the group a few times, but I was just surviving at that point. I’m really proud of how I kept fighting and arrived at the finish totally spent. My next big goal is Amstel on April 20th. I hope I can recover well from Flanders and have an even better race at Amstel!”

Spring is where her flowers bloom.🌼
Up next: Amstel Gold. You don’t want to miss it.

📸: @jeredgruber

The Sleep-Hormone Cycle: A Vicious Loop

Hormonal imbalances can lead to poor sleep quality, and poor sleep, in turn, can exacerbate hormone dysregulation. For example, inadequate sleep can increase cortisol levels, reduce melatonin production, and lead to insulin resistance—all of which further disrupt your body’s natural sleep-wake cycle.

Supporting your body with plant-powered solutions like Juna’s Nightcap Sleep Gummies can help restore hormonal balance, improve sleep quality, and enhance overall wellness. These gummies are formulated with natural ingredients like Phytomelatonin, Chamomile Extract, GABA, and Passionflower Extract, which work synergistically to calm the mind, reduce stress, and promote deep, restful sleep.

Sweet, savory and creamy. 😍 Try our Italian Sausage Ravioli with cream, caramelized onion and chives. Everyone will love it! 🧡

Timing: 15 minutes
Serves: 4

One 20 oz package Giovanni Rana Italian Sausage Ravioli
3 tbsp butter, divided
1 ½ tbsp flour
½ cup milk
½ cup sour cream
2 tbsp chives
1 medium yellow onion, cut into 1/8 inch strips
Salt and fresh ground pepper

In a medium pan, melt 1 ½ tbsp of butter on medium heat. Add onions and cook until soft and turn golden brown. Set aside.
In a large pan, heat sour cream on low. Season with salt and pepper. Do not boil to prevent curdling/ separation. Fold in the sour cream and caramelized onions. Season with salt & pepper.
Cook ravioli according to packaging instructions. Strain and toss ravioli in the pan with the sauce. Sprinkle with chives and serve.

Here are some HOT tips for hair that “doesn’t hold a curl” 👇🏼

Spray with hairspray FIRST and brush through - always use heat protection too✨ Aquage Working spray is perfect for this. 

CURL with a flat-iron (or wand) instead of a traditional curling iron (depending on desired style and hair type). A flat iron can allow more even heat distribution while smoothing at the same time.

Wait until the last minute to brush out and use a wide-toothed comb and move slowly while reinforcing with a working spray. 

Finish with a high-hold hairspray 8-10 inches away from the hair (this will help with even distribution of product) ✨

“When I started Willy Chavarria, my intention was gender fluidity. The industry, though, is still structured around gendered categories. When I design, I don’t think about gender at all. My sketches are just a head, a circle and body made of straight lines — no [genitalia].” 
 
Centring Latinx influences and gender fluidity in American fashion — recent years have cemented California-hailing ascendant @willychavarrianewyork as one of the world’s most urgent, coveted design forces. Courted by A-list fans and with social messages more pressing than ever before, 10 years since his eponymous label’s inception, it’s crossing new frontiers on a regular basis. Covering our Spring/Summer 2025 issue, he talks his monumental January Paris Fashion Week debut, disregarding gender in the design process, marrying his West and East Coast histories and how Chicano culture defines his brand’s DNA. Plus, he answers questions from a bevy of friends, fans and collaborators, including @kingofbingo, @juliafox, @leonbridges and @paoramos. Head to manabouttown.tv to pre-order the issue now!

“Who gets to define Americana?”

For Willy Chavarria, the answer has never been the status quo. From workwear to Catholic rosaries, exaggerated collars to the streets of Fresno, his runways aren’t just fashion—they’re statements, protests, love letters to a world that has tried to erase people like him. His latest collection, Tarantula, debuted just as the U.S. doubled down on stripping identities and histories. Chavarria resists, reclaims, and reimagines. Shot beside one of his muses, Paloma Elsesser, this cover story celebrates Willy and his community, sending the message that “How we love is who we are.”

A Special Note from Our Co-Founder, Amberlee 💙

20 years ago, long before candles were part of my journey, I had the incredible honor of being a founding member of DanceBlue at the University of Kentucky. 🎗️

DanceBlue is a fully student-run organization dedicated to raising funds year-round for the DanceBlue Hematology/Oncology Clinic. The event culminates in a 24-hour, no sitting, no sleeping dance marathon. Since 2006, more than $23 million has been raised to support pediatric cancer research and treatment. This weekend in Lexington, over 1,000 students are coming together to lead and participate in this extraordinary event.

I could easily write a book about my passion for DanceBlue—a passion that sparked my journey in design and has shaped my path as an entrepreneur. It’s a privilege to return each year to contribute in new ways.

Earlier this year, we introduced a special collaboration: our DanceBlue Reusable Rocks Glass Candle. This unique candle captures the spirit of this incredible cause and serves as a meaningful keepsake long after it’s burned. ✨

These Jet-Puffed Color Changers Marshmallows are like a mood ring for your springtime s’mores ☁️🌷

Choose your own dessert adventure with gooey marshmallows dunked in chocolate and caramel, topped with a sweet or salty twist😛

Ingredients
1 Bag Jet-Puffed Jumbo Marshmallows
Colorful Candy Melts 
Festive Sprinkles
How to Make It

1. Press a mini flower cookie cutter into the center of a Jet-Puffed Jumbo Marshmallow.
2. Insert a skewer into the bottom of the marshmallow.
3. Fill the shape of the flower with a colorful candy melt over parchment paper.
4. Decorate with festive sprinkles and candies.
5. Let set for 10 minutes to dry, then tie together with a bow for a beautiful bouquet!

🍫🔥 Jet-Puffed S’mores Ice Cream Sandwiches🍦Toasted or not, these are a must for your dessert lineup!

Ingredients (Makes 6 sandwiches):
12 graham cracker squares
½ cup Jet-Puffed Marshmallow Creme
2 cups ice cream of your choice
1 cup semi sweet chocolate chips or melting chocolate

Instructions:
1. Line a small baking sheet or shallow pan with parchment paper. Spread the ice cream into a flat, even layer about ½  inch thick. Freeze until firm, at least 30 minutes.
2. Spread a generous layer of Jet-Puffed Marshmallow Creme onto one side of each graham cracker. Optional: For a toasted touch, lightly toast the creme with a kitchen torch or broiler.
3. Once frozen, cut the ice cream into squares the size of your graham crackers.Sandwich each ice cream square between two marshmallow-covered grahams, sticky sides facing in.
4. Melt chocolate chips in 30-second intervals in the microwave, stirring until smooth. Drizzle or dip the tops of the sandwiches with chocolate.
5. Place the assembled sandwiches on a parchment-lined tray and freeze for at least 1 hour, or until ready to serve. Then, pull from the freezer and serve immediately for the ultimate frozen s’mores treat!

A fruity-fun flavor explosion you never saw coming🍊🍓🍋🍋‍🟩 Are you going to try it? We dare you!

Ingredients:
1 Bag Jet-Puffed Fruity-Fun Mini Marshmallows 
1 Jar Jet-Puffed Marshmallow Creme 
8oz Philadelphia Cream Cheese 
1 Tablespoon Vanilla Extract

How to Make It:
1. Mix Jet-Puffed Marshmallow Creme, softened Philadelphia cream cheese and vanilla in a bowl.
2. Fold in Jet-Puffed Fruity-Fun Mini Marshmallows with a spatula.
3. Refrigerate until ready to serve with your favorite crackers or fruit. Enjoy!

Spread your wings and enjoy a flutter of sweetness with colorful butterfly marshmallows 🦋🧁

Ingredients:
1 Bag Jet-Puffed Regular Marshmallows
Colorful Sprinkles 
Frosting
Pastel Candies

How to Make It:
1. Cut a regular marshmallow in half. 
2. Cut the marshmallow halves 3/4 of the way up, then fold over one side to make a V shape.
3. Dip the sticky side of the marshmallow into colorful sprinkles.
4. Arrange pastel candies into the shape of a butterfly on frosting.
5. Place marshmallows on both sides of the candies to look like butterfly wings.

@jeremyrenner says his near-fatal accident helped him zoom out on life and let go of the “white noise” that once consumed him. He now values simplicity, peace and being present.

‘My Next Breath’ is an intimate narrative about the incident that changed my life and what it taught me about inner strength, endurance, and hope as I overcame insurmountable odds to recover, one breath at a time. Listen to me tell my story, with a note written and read by my daughter Ava, now on Audible.

@jeremyrenner credits “the simplicity of just breathing” with saving his life, as he waited for paramedics after breaking more than 38 bones when he was crushed beneath a Snowcat on New Year’s Day in 2023.

Renner’s new book, “My Next Breath,” tells the story of the accident and his recovery, which he says was fueled by his daughter Ava: “She gets better if I get better.”

"We were working on the long, winding driveway that climbs to an expansive parking area in front of my house. I was in the cab of the snowcat, and my nephew Alex was on the ground attaching the Ford truck to the back of the snowcat with chains. We started pulling the truck out of the snow and got it unstuck. Alex went to unlatch it from the snowcat as I started to turn the snowcat around. But its snowblade was up high and I couldn’t quite see Alex, who was somewhere in front of me. I got out of the driver’s seat and stepped on the tracks to talk to him.⁠
⁠
“Before exiting the driver’s cab! — Apply parking brake,” the manual says. But I didn’t engage the parking brake, or disengage the steel tracks. In that moment — an innocent, critical, life-changing moment — that tiny but monumental slip of the mind would change the course of my life for ever" | ✍️ Jeremy Renner⁠

“I Met My Solitude” | Collage on Panel - now showing in my solo exhibition “stills” @garnernarrative. The opening reception is next Sunday 5/18 from 2-5PM.

This piece is named after the poem by Naomi Replansky. 

The poem begins with, “I met my Solitude. We two stood glaring.
I had to tremble, meeting her face to face.
Then she saying, and I with bent head hearing:
“You sent me forth to exile and disgrace,
 
“Most faithful of your friends, then most forsaken,
Forgotten in breast, in bath, in books, in bed.
To someone else you gave the gifts I gave you,
And you embraced another in my stead.…”

📷: @bethgarrabrant

Back in the office… 😎 
#MiamiTSTheErasTour

The Eras Tour is BACK and the 3 Miami crowds we just got to play for were on a new level. With only 5 cities left to play before it’s over, I knew I was going to be savoring every moment up on that stage but the bewildering passion of those crowds really blew my mind. It rained (a lot) the 1st and 3rd nights, and so that kicked up the cinematic drama. I had really missed this on our break. The mass quantities of joyful people genuinely living in the moment and seeming truly carefree for 3.5 hours. My mystifyingly talented friend @florence came to Miami and each night we performed “Florida!!!” in Florida!!! I got some new outfits, and it’s always nice when the crowd notices that 😁 You guys are just the best. Thank you to everyone who came and everyone who followed along online. 4 more cities left and the next one up is: New Orleans!

📷: @johnshearer / @gettyimages / TAS Rights Management

Our 6 shows in Toronto were so incredible. It was awesome to play in Canada after so much time. As always, the fans in Toronto treated us like it was a hometown show. Couldn’t have asked for more love or generosity from the people who came out. I got to play a mashup of the *Grammy nominated* song ‘us’ with @gracieabrams, mashed up with ‘Out of the Woods’ and I just adore her. She’s been giving the most amazing performances every night on this tour!! The emotions have gotten pretty heightened for me and the rest of the team because it’s gotten extremely real for us: Our next city will be the last one of The Eras Tour, and the closing of the most extraordinary chapter of my life so far. See you 🔜 , Vancouver. We can’t wait to give you all we’ve got for three more shows. 🥲

AND for all International fans, I’m excited to tell you The Tortured Poets Department: The Anthology will be available to you online starting 29 Nov at 1pm GMT along with The Official Eras Tour Book starting 7 Dec at 1pm GMT 🫶

📷: @emmaeliza / @gettyimages / TAS Rights Management

Couldn’t have asked for a more magical way to end our US shows on The Eras Tour. Just had the time of my life with 207,000 beautiful people in Indianapolis who showered us with so much love and excitement and joy… I know I’ll be looking back on this weekend and smiling because it was just like a dreamscape, all of it. Thank you to everyone who came out to see us on our last 3 American shows!! And here’s a friendly but extremely important reminder that tomorrow is the US Election and your last chance to vote. 🗳️ 🇺🇸 
There are only 9 shows left on The Eras Tour. I can’t believe we’re in single digits 🥲 Next up: getting to finally see my beloved Canadian fans again!! See you 🔜 for 6 shows in Toronto!

📷: @kevinmazur / @gettyimages / TAS Rights Management

Wow, New Orleans. I’m still smiling thinking about that wonderful weekend. The city really welcomed us with open arms (with friendship bracelets on those metaphorical arms) and celebrated the tour with such flare. One of the things I’ll always remember from this weekend was getting to surprise the crowd with a performance by the pop princess of our dreams: @sabrinacarpenter. Side note: She had one day off from her very exhaustive tour schedule. Her show is physically full on and spectacular, and she could’ve been resting in her time off. One of the reasons I respect her so much is that she does things like this, goes out of her way to give fans a surprise moment they didn’t expect. She’s as real as they come and I’m so thankful she did that for us. Thank you to every one of those beautiful faces I got to see on 3 magical nights in Louisiana. Our next stop is our last US city on The Eras Tour: Indianapolis ♥️

😂🗣️ Andrea Pirlo’s story about attacking Gattuso with a fire extinguisher: 

“One time we gave Gattuso a soaking with a fire extinguisher. We draw away to the Republic of Ireland which meant we qualified for the 2010 World Cup and so the last group game, against Cyprus, had become almost like a friendly. ⚽️

Pretty much meaningless, and that’s exactly how we treated it.

The manager gave us a night off, and almost all of us went out for dinner. Gattuso didn’t – he stayed at the team hotel. When we got back, we were very drunk, and we ended up chatting in the lounge. 🍻 

We weren’t tired, so we needed to find something to pass the time. Everyone had the same idea: “Let’s go and p*** off Gattuso.” 😂

He was already asleep, with his little nightcap on his head. On the way up the stairs to his room, De Rossi spotted a fire extinguisher. 🧯

“I’m off to put out Gattuso,” he said. We knocked on the door and out Gattuso came, screwing his eyes up as he advanced. Daniele started spraying, covering him in every last drop before running off to hide in his room. 💦 

He left me at the mercy of that monster in its underpants, absolutely dripping with foam and shouting total gibberish. 😡

Listening to him, I knew he was beginning to wake up and regain his senses. I tried to escape, but I was already done for. 

When the guy after you is Gattuso, and he’s out to do you harm, you can run as hard as you like, but he will always catch you. He gave me a full range of slaps.” 👊

Your calling is going to crush you.

💔If you are called to mend to the brokenhearted, you are going to wrestle with a broken heart. 

👦🏻If you are called to heal God’s little ones, you are going to experience your own share of trauma. 

🪨If you’re called to preach and teach the gospel, you WILL be sifted for the wisdom that anoints your message. 

🪞If you are called to empower, your self-esteem will be attacked- your successes hard fought. 

⚔️Your calling will come with spiritual warfare and a sifting - BOTH are necessary for your mantle to be authentic, humble and powerful. 

Your crushing won’t be easy because your assignment is not easy - and you can’t minister POWERFULLY what you haven’t walked out. Read that sentence again. 

🕊When you’re feeling the weight of it coming down on you, RUN to the Father who longs to be your comfort. Let him whisper your true identity over you while resting under the shadow of his wings. Position yourself against his heartbeat. Let him renew your strength and set your eyes forward. No olives, no oil. No grapes, no wine.

Your oil is not cheap my friend.

Author: Hannah Williamson
